      "side": 1,
      "message": "Simply speaking, interface in golang is implemented implicitly (unlike C++/Java where you will see `Class MyClass: public MyInterface` or `class MyClass implements MyInterface`. So here, this is ensuring (*client) dose implement the `tree.Client` interface so that if anything changes in the `tree.Client` interface (e.g. new method added, method signature changed), the compiler will complain here.\n\nSince it serves for type checking purpose only, so this variable is useless. That\u0027s why it is `var _`. Also, we don\u0027t need to initialize it as `\u0026client{}` to create unnecessary memory footprint, (*client)(nil) is sufficient.",
